      <P><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Not only does the Schwab 1000 Fund provide investors with broad exposure to companies in many different industries and of many different sizes, but part of its stated strategy is to consider the tax consequences of its investment decisions in an effort to help reduce the tax burden on its shareholders. It&#146;s a strategy that seems to have paid off.</font></P>
      <P align=center><FONT face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color=#669999 
      size=3>Since its inception in April of 1991, the Schwab 
      1000 Fund <BR>has <B>yet to pay a capital gain distribution</B>. This 
      doesn&#8217;t <BR>guarantee that it will never do so, but it does help 
      illustrate<BR>the effectiveness of its <B><a href="http://schwab.ed10.net/ud/FSXF/7M5B/1C0Q/RF/UUL2JZ">tax-smart 
      strategy</a></B>.</FONT></P>
